[117688937161238303810,100042782689821233210,We went knowing we might not get in. But we lucked out both times :o) The service was very efficient. It's a small place but hopping. I am not a fan of the "dutch" pancakes, but that is a personal choice. They remind me of crepes and I don't like crepes. However, their "american" pancakes were amazing. And their savory pancakes hit the spot for my husband. They even give you a cute wooden shoe key chain when you pay your bill. I would go back to Amsterdam just for their pancakes :o)]
